refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
stringfalsestrrchr stringhaystack stringneedle boolbefore_needle&false;
This function returns the portion of haystack which starts at the last occurrence of needle and goes until the end of haystack.

&reftitle.returnvalues;


 This function returns the portion of string, or &false; if
 needle is not found.

&reftitle.changelog;





    &Version;
    &Description;





    8.3.0

     The before_needle parameter was added.


   &strings.changelog.needle-empty;


    8.0.0

     Passing an &integer; as needle is no longer supported.




    7.3.0

     Passing an &integer; as needle has been deprecated.

  &reftitle.examples;



    strrchr example


<?php
$ext = strrchr('somefile.txt', '.');
echo "file extension: $ext \n";
$ext = $ext ? strtolower(substr($ext, 1)) : '';
echo "file extension: $ext";
?>


    &example.outputs.similar;


file extension: .txt
file extension: txt
